# Deterministic line endings for vendored-integrity hashing (HELM-REL-2).
#
# hub/vendored/** is byte-hashed against MANIFEST.json (scripts/verify-vendored.mjs,
# HELM-SEC-3 / THREAT-MODEL §5 F3). Without this file, a Windows clone with
# core.autocrlf=true rewrites LF->CRLF on checkout and every hash mismatches, while
# Linux CI stays green (known CRLF-vendor trap, memory project-ainumbers-gpu3-land-lessons).
#
# `* text=auto eol=lf` (repo-wide) chosen over a path-scoped `hub/vendored/** -text`:
# it normalizes ALL tracked text to LF on checkout regardless of platform or local
# core.autocrlf, so every future vendor path/kernel drop is covered automatically
# instead of requiring a new attributes line each time.
* text=auto eol=lf
